text: Lake Creek is a stream in Calhoun and Pocahontas counties, Iowa, in the United States. It is a tributary of the North Raccoon River. Lake Creek was named from the fact it flowed from a lake. ==See also== *List of rivers of Iowa ==References== Category:Bodies of water of Calhoun County, Iowa Category:Bodies of water of Pocahontas County, Iowa Category:Rivers of Iowa
title: Lake Creek (Raccoon River tributary)
